President Biden has declared a major disaster in the Commonwealth of Virginia due to flooding and mudslides that occurred from July 13 to July 14, 2022. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding is available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Charles Monroe Maltbie III has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations, and additional designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.